Picture: Eugene Coetzee Police, responding to a shooting on Tuesday afternoon, have found the body of a man in Sidon Road, North End. Police spokeswoman Colonel Priscilla Naidu said it was not yet clear what had happened. She said police arrived at the scene to find the body lying near a parked car. The gang unit has also been called to the scene to ascertain if this is possibly a gang-related incident, she said. Police are still on the scene. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share